<h4>FAQs for EO about the website</h4>


<h5><strong>1. I cannot find my password/username to login?
</strong></h5>
<p>
    Please contact <a href="gmorrison@plos.org">gmorrison@plos.org </a>with your user name if known, first name, last name. 
 <br />
    <span>Note: When contacting <a href="gmorrison@plos.org">gmorrison@plos.org </a>please ensure you quote ‘ARRIVE’ in the subject line of your email. </span>
</p>
<h5><strong>2. The website is not working, I am getting an error message/The website is very slow </strong></h5>
<p>Please contact <a href="gmorrison@plos.org">gmorrison@plos.org </a>with a brief description of the situation including what browser you are using, time that this occurred  <span>and a screen shot if possible. </span></p>
<h5><strong>3. I am not sure if this manuscript reports a laboratory-based in vivo animal research?
</strong></h5>
<p>
    Please check our Appendix for further information on what kinds of studies this refers to. If you are still uncertain please contact <a href="gmorrison@plos.org">gmorrison@plos.org</a> with manuscript number and title.
</p>
<h5><strong>4. I’ve added the ARRIVE flag by mistake and I have already randomized a manuscript. What should I do? </strong></h5>
<p>Please contact <a href="gmorrison@plos.org">gmorrison@plos.org </a>with manuscript number and title. </p>
<h5><strong>5. I have added the ARRIVE flag to a manuscript and entered it in our gdoc but I have forgotten to randomize a the manuscript in the system, what should I do? </strong></h5>
<p>Please contact <a href="gmorrison@plos.org">gmorrison@plos.org </a>with manuscript number and title.  </p>
<h5><strong>6. The Corresponding Author has more than one affiliation so which one should I use in the drop down menu ‘Country of Corresponding Author’? </strong></h5>
<p>Please use the one that is most common to the rest of the authors. If this is not possible, please choose one and leave a note about this in the comments box. </p>
<h5><strong>7. I can’t find a manuscript by searching it. </strong></h5>
<p>Please make sure that the manuscript number entered is exactly the same as the original and that there are no spaces at the end or at the beginning. If you are still having difficulties, please contact <a href="gmorrison@plos.org">gmorrison@plos.org </a>with manuscript number and title. </p>
<h5><strong>8. The paper that I am tech checking describes both laboratory-based *and* field research involving live animals. Should I enter this paper into the randomization engine or not?   </strong></h5>
<p>In cases such as the one you describe we will want to err on the side of caution. We ask that if you do encounter such a situation to please do enter the manuscript details into the engine but also add a comment explaining the issue.  </p>

